# Copy this file to connected_mcps.txt and list every claude.ai-managed MCP
# you've authenticated. Auto-tune uses this list to decide which subagents
# can install (e.g. designer-content needs Atlassian).
#
# The auth cache at ~/.claude/mcp-needs-auth-cache.json only tracks MCPs that
# *need* auth — once authenticated, an MCP disappears from that cache. So this
# file is the source of truth for "authenticated and ready."
#
# One MCP name per line. Lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# Common entries (uncomment and authenticate via /mcp inside Claude Code):
# claude_ai_Atlassian_Rovo
# claude_ai_Slack
# claude_ai_Microsoft_365
# claude_ai_Zoom_for_Claude
